content.text:
- **Carrick Therapeutics Announces First Patient Dosed in Phase 1 Clinical Trial of CT7439 (CDK12/13 Inhibitor)**
  - URL: `https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/news-media/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase`
  - Quote snippets:
    - “CT7439, a novel cyclin dependent kinase 12/13 (CDK12/13) inhibitor / Cyclin-K glue-degrader.”
    - “Clinical trial details can also be found on www.clinicaltrials.gov under study ID: NCT06600789.”
    - “The clinical trial is enrolling patients with advanced solid tumors, including ovarian, breast and Ewing's Sarcoma.” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/news-media/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase))

- **JCI — CDK12/13 inactivation triggers STING-mediated antitumor immunity in preclinical models**
  - URL: `https://www.jci.org/articles/view/193745`
  - Quote snippets:
    - “Using an orally bioavailable proteolysis-targeting chimera (PROTAC) degrader of CDK12/13, YJ1206 (20)”
    - “a molecular glue degrader of cyclin K, CT7439, which inhibits CDK12/13, has progressed to a phase I clinical trial (ClinicalTrials.gov NCT06600789)” ([jci.org](https://www.jci.org/articles/view/193745))

- **Trial | NCT06600789 — A Modular Phase 1/2 Study With CT7439 in Participants With Solid Malignancies**
  - URL: `https://cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu/trial/NCT06600789/`
  - Quote snippets:
    - “A Modular Phase 1/2 Study With CT7439 in Participants With Solid Malignancies”
    - “CT7439 Capsules (0.5 mg, 1mg, 3mg)” ([cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu](https://cdek.pharmacy.purdue.edu/trial/NCT06600789/))

- **Non-enzymatic SETD1A activity drives breast cancer cell proliferation via cyclin K (Breast Cancer Research; 2025)**
  - URL: `https://breast-cancer-research.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s13058-025-02101-x`
  - Quote snippets:
    - “CT7439, a dual inhibitor of CDK12/13 and a cyclin K glue degrader, is now in phase I/II clinical trial for advanced solid tumors, including breast cancer (NCT06600789).”
    - “The cyclin K degrader CR8 is effective for the growth of TNBC cells” ([breast-cancer-research.biomedcentral.com](https://breast-cancer-research.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s13058-025-02101-x))

- **Therapeutic Targeting of CDK12/CDK13 in Triple-Negative Breast Cancer (Cancer Cell)**
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/`
  - Quote snippets:
    - “Here we report the development of SR-4835, a highly selective dual inhibitor of CDK12 and CDK13, which disables triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC) cells.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/))

- **Noncovalent CDK12/13 dual inhibitors-based PROTACs degrade CDK12-Cyclin K complex and induce synthetic lethality with PARP inhibitor (Eur J Med Chem)**
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/`
  - Quote snippets:
    - “we have synthesized a potent PROTAC degrader PP-C8 based on the noncovalent dual inhibitors of CDK12/13”
    - “PP-C8 demonstrates profound synergistic antiproliferative effects with PARP inhibitor in triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC).” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))

- **Discovery of a Highly Potent and Selective Dual PROTAC Degrader of CDK12 and CDK13 (ACS; full text on PMC)**
  - URL: `https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC9876424/`
  - Quote snippets:
    - “The optimal compound 7f effectively degraded CDK12 and CDK13 with DC_{50} values of 2.2 and 2.1 nM, respectively”
    - “7f markedly inhibited proliferation of multiple TNBC cell lines including MFM223” ([pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC9876424/))

- **A phase 1 study with dose expansion of the CDK inhibitor dinaciclib (SCH 727965) in combination with epirubicin in patients with metastatic triple negative breast cancer (Invest New Drugs)**
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25947565/`
  - Quote snippets:
    - “dinaciclib (SCH 727965)”
    - “Trial registration:  ClinicalTrials.gov NCT01624441.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25947565/))

- **Degradation of CCNK/CDK12 is a druggable vulnerability of colorectal cancer (Cell Reports)**
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34289372/`
  - Quote snippets:
    - “NCT02 is identified as a candidate with minimal risk of non-specific toxicity.”
    - “NCT02 acts as molecular glue that induces ubiquitination of cyclin K (CCNK) and proteasomal degradation of CCNK and its complex partner CDK12.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34289372/))

- **Exploiting targeted degradation of cyclins and cyclin-dependent kinases for cancer therapeutics: a review (PMC)**
  - URL: `https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12390393/`
  - Quote snippets:
    - “Selective CDK12 PROTACs include Molecule 50 (BSJ-4-116) and Molecule 51 (PP-C8)”
    - “Representative compounds include CR8, DS17/30, compound 21195, SR-4835, HQ461, NCT02” ([pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12390393/))
